      void BulkCaseProcessor.withEachCase(nuix.Case currentCaseFromGui, CaseConsumer caseWorkFunction)
      Begins iterating provided list of cases, passing the following information for each case to the provided callback: - The case object - Information about the case - Current index of the case provided - Total number of cases to be iterated This method differs from BulkCaseProcessor.withEachCase(CaseConsumer) in that you provide the currently open case in the GUI (in Ruby this would usually be $current_case).
